OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FThe National Trust has launched a rare
OL,8,Fcampaign asking the public to contact
OL,9,Ftheir MPs to call for an urgent
OL,10,Fincrease in action to reverse nature's
OL,11,F"freefall" in the UK.
OL,13,FThe call, which director-general
OL,14,FHilary McGrady said has not been
OL,15,Flaunched "lightly", comes as polling
OL,16,Ffor the National Trust reveals
OL,17,Frestoring nature is important for
OL,18,Fvoters of all political hues.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@JO]wD@JOUwD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FBut people believe the Government
OL,8,Fcares less about it than they do
OL,9,Fthemselves, the polling of 4,000
OL,10,Fpeople by More in Common for the trust
OL,11,Ffound.
OL,13,FThe survey also found the UK's
OL,14,Fcountryside and nature is second only
OL,15,Fto the NHS as a source of pride for
OL,16,FBritons.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FAnd it found that policies to weaken
OL,8,Fwildlife and nature protections in the
OL,9,Fplanning system to boost development
OL,10,Fwere unpopular with voters across the
OL,11,Fboard.
OL,13,FThe UK's biggest conservation charity
OL,14,Fsaid the country is one of the most
OL,15,Fnature-depleted in the world, with
OL,16,Fmillions of birds disappearing from
OL,17,Fthe skies in recent decades and just
OL,18,F14% of English rivers in good
OL,19,Fecological health.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FHowever, the trust said, the
OL,8,FGovernment did not appear to be taking
OL,9,Fthe issue seriously enough, pointing
OL,10,Fto the Prime Minister and Chancellor's
OL,11,Frecent comments describing wildlife
OL,12,Fsuch as bats, snails and newts as
OL,13,F"blockers" to development and new
OL,14,Fhousing.
OL,16,FIt is the first time in 15 years the
OL,17,FNational Trust has launched a campaign
OL,18,Fto ask its members and the public to
OL,19,Fput pressure on the Government to
OL,20,Fchange course.
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FThe charity said its mobilisation over
OL,8,Fplanning reforms in 2011 helped secure
OL,9,Fsignificant changes to the policy.
OL,11,FThis time it is asking for the
OL,12,FGovernment to honour its commitment to
OL,13,Fmanage 30% of land for nature by 2030
OL,14,F` the so-called 30X3 pledge made under
OL,15,Fthe Tories ` with more designated
OL,16,Fspace for wildlife and paying farmers
OL,17,Fproperly to help nature thrive.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FThe trust also wants a Government
OL,8,Fcommitment to stop weakening laws that
OL,9,Fprotect nature, and bring in a strong
OL,10,Fwater reform Bill to clean up rivers
OL,11,Fand seas and make polluters pay for
OL,12,Ftheir harms.
OL,14,FAnd it is calling for the Government
OL,15,Fto commit to ensuring neighbourhoods
OL,16,Fare rich in nature, and ending unfair
OL,17,Faccess to green spaces.
OL,19,FMs McGrady said: "We would never
OL,20,Flaunch a campaign like this lightly.
OL,26,@{D@ROU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,F"But nature is in a state of freefall
OL,8,Fin this country and our Government
OL,9,Fdoesn't appear to be taking the issue
OL,10,Fseriously enough.
OL,12,F"In fact, it seems way behind voters
OL,13,Fon this incredibly important issue.
OL,15,F"So we're calling on the public to ask
OL,16,Ftheir MP to step up."
OL,18,FShe said that regardless of people's
OL,19,Fpolitical views, they had a shared
OL,20,Flove of nature ` calling it "a major
OL,21,Fsource of pride and a unifier".
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@AOUwD@AOUxD@UO]|D@]OU}D@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,F"Our research shows that wanting to
OL,8,Frestore nature is the mainstream view;
OL,9,Fit is the Government that is out of
OL,10,Fstep."
OL,12,FShe added: "Nature is essential for
OL,13,Four economic prosperity, for national
OL,14,Fsecurity, for our wellbeing and for
OL,15,Fall our futures.
OL,17,F"It's time politicians listened to the
OL,18,Felectorate and started to implement
OL,19,Fchange."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@FO]tD@LOUyD@AOU{D@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FThe survey shows nearly a quarter of
OL,8,Fpeople (24%) think restoring nature in
OL,9,Fthe UK is a top priority ` with more
OL,10,Fthan a third of Labour voters (36%)
OL,11,Ftaking that view ` while a further 59%
OL,12,Fthink it is important.
OL,14,FMore than half (54%) think the UK
OL,15,Fgovernment has the lead responsibility
OL,16,Ffor restoring nature in this country,
OL,17,Fbut just 13% believe it to be top
OL,18,Fpriority and 36% think it is important
OL,19,Fto the current administration.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,FAnd six in 10 people quizzed (59%)
OL,8,Fthink the Government cares less than
OL,9,Fthey do personally about restoring
OL,10,Fnature, the polling found.
OL,12,FLuke Tryl, executive director (UK) of
OL,13,FMore in Common, said the findings laid
OL,14,Fbare the risk for Labour of appearing
OL,15,Fas an anti-nature party.
OL,17,F"Britons of all political stripes are
OL,18,Fnature-lovers, but the majority of the
OL,19,Fpublic thinks the Government cares
OL,20,Fless about nature than they do.
OL,26,@yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30511
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1774085867
OL,3,CNational Trust urges public to lobby
OL,4,Cpoliticians to reverse nature
OL,5,C'freefall'
OL,7,F"With Labour voters being more likely
OL,8,Fthan those of any other political
OL,9,Fparty to say that restoring nature is
OL,10,Fa top priority, the Government may
OL,11,Ffind itself on the wrong side of
OL,12,Fpublic opinion ` and its own voters."
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@eO]
